Interface SemanticRestriction.DataExactRestriction<S extends org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLObject,A extends org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLAxiom>

  • Type Parameters:

    public static interface SemanticRestriction.DataExactRestriction<S extends org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLObject,A extends org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLAxiom>
extends SemanticRestriction.PropertyCardinalityRestriction<S,A,org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLDataProperty,org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLDataRange>
    It implements the getRestriction(OWLReferencesInterface) for exact cardinality restriction over a data property. It is applicable to a SemanticRestriction.getSubject(), through SemanticRestriction.getAxiom(OWLReferencesInterface), to be added or removed in an ontology. Indeed it calls: ontology.getOWLFactory().getOWLDataExactCardinality( {@link #getCardinality()}, {@link #getProperty()}, getValue}.
